The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 18 January is 172,822 (19,918.7 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 13 January, there were 7,121 new confirmed cases (820.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 06 January, there were 11,852 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 40% (4,731 fewer cases).
